In an eNCA exclusive interview, ANC Secretary General, Ace Magashule says he is not corrupt. Magashule appeared in the Bloemfontein Magistrate's Court. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - In an exclusive eNCA interview, ANC Secretary-General Ace Magashule has defended his reputation saying he is not corrupt. "I'm not corrupt. Never in my history have I done any corruption. For many years, I've been at the helm of political powers and office. I can't be, after so many years of struggle, become corrupt. I welcome the charges." READ: Ace Magashule takes aim at SA media Magashule says he is not bothered by his former personal assistant turning state witness. " She must say whatever she knows. That will be fine. I want anybody who thinks I'm corrupt to get this platform now. Let them be called to give evidence. Let the South African people judge. READ: ANC has been infiltrated: Magashule Magashule appeared in the Bloemfontein Magistrate's Court on Friday facing 21 charges of fraud, corruption and money laundering. Watch the full interview in the video above.